  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Monroe County IL?",
  "response": "When searching for a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Monroe County, IL, it's important to consider factors such as the types of treatment offered, the facility's reputation, and its success rates. Here are a few options you might want to consider:\n\n1. **Chestnut Health Systems**\n   - **Location:** Located nearby in Belleville, IL (which is in St. Clair County, adjacent to Monroe County)\n   - **Services:** Offers comprehensive substance abuse treatment, including inpatient and outpatient services, detox, and specialized programs for adolescents and adults.\n   - **Contact:** You can reach them at (618) 829-2700 or visit their website at [Chestnut Health Systems](https://www.chestnut.org/).\n\n2. **Gibson Recovery Center**\n   - **Location:** Located in Cape Girardeau, MO, which is about an hour's drive from Monroe County, IL.\n   - **Services:** Provides inpatient treatment for substance abuse, including medical detox, individual and group therapy, and aftercare planning.\n   - **Contact:** You can reach them at (573) 334-5513 or visit their website at [Gibson Recovery Center](https://www.gibsonrecoverycenter.com/).\n\n3. **Sana Lake Recovery Center**\n   - **Location:** Located in Dittmer, MO, which is also about an hour's drive from Monroe County, IL.\n   - **Services:** Offers a full continuum of care including detox, residential treatment, and outpatient services with a focus on personalized treatment plans.\n   - **Contact:** You can reach them at (844) 726-2144 or visit their website at [Sana Lake Recovery Center](https://www.sanalake.com/).\n\nAlthough these centers are not located directly in Monroe County, they are within a reasonable distance and offer comprehensive treatment options for those seeking help with drug and alcohol addiction.\n\nIt's recommended to contact these facilities directly to inquire about their specific programs, insurance acceptance, and availability. Additionally, speaking with a healthcare provider or a substance abuse counselor can help you find the best fit for your or your loved one's needs.",
